X

XmlDocumentJsonHandler - Class in net.markenwerk.utils.json.common.handler
A XmlDocumentJsonHandler is a JsonHandler that creates a XML Document that represents the same data as the handled JSON document using the following rules: A JSON array is represented as a tag with name array. A JSON object is represented as a tag with name object. A JSON object entry is represented as a tag with name entry.
XmlDocumentJsonHandler() - Constructor for class net.markenwerk.utils.json.common.handler.XmlDocumentJsonHandler
Creates a new XmlDocumentJsonHandler using a @link default DocumentBuilder created by a default DocumentBuilderFactory.
XmlDocumentJsonHandler(DocumentBuilder) - Constructor for class net.markenwerk.utils.json.common.handler.XmlDocumentJsonHandler
Create a new XmlDocumentJsonHandler using the given DocumentBuilder to create a new XML Document.
